result.name: ‎Tsui Wah Restaurant

reviews.text: I love the place for its food with great taste.. A bit salty, not suitable for people who don't like salty food 食物重口味. Perfect place for a late supper

Just left at 1130 pm at night because after waiting 30 minutes, they had messed up the whole restaurants orders, lied to us when we’re sitting next to the kitchen that food was being prepared and needed 20 minutes when other dishes that usually take that long were given to others first. Literally, five people complained and left at the same time. Terrible service.
This place take you 30 minutes to get you the food and it’s over priced. They turn the air conditioner high in order to kick you out quickly. Bad customer services , everything just bad

A local franchise popular with locals and Tourists alike. The restaurant opens till early morning. See of its signature dishes include Hong Kong Style Milk Tea, Condensed Milk Crispy Bun, Jumbo Hot Dog and many more.

Beautiful Tsui Wah with standard pricing .. got big table for 8, and little private room too. We ordered oven bake pork chop with rice, very juicy and big portion, fresh king prawn with dry noodle and fried okra egg fu-young.. egg was smooth and all very yum yum. 

The bonus was not busy at night, so would definitely come here more often.

result.name: 翠華餐廳

reviews.text: 都幾好，不過早餐都唔係平，可能在灣仔租金貴，遲啲去試吓其他地區先，可以試吓不錯之選擇。
此分店舖面不算很寬敞，但店員服務值得一讚，到訪當日正在下大雨，客人進出令餐廳四處濕滑， 店員不厭其煩一邊清理積水，一邊 提醒客人小心，一邊應付嗰個客人的要求，表現專業。
